         <div>
            <head>17.9.1882 Sonntag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49069">Hamburg</placeName> September 17. 1882</p>
            <p> Arrived here tonight after having stopped 2 hours at <placeName key="48985">Bremen</placeName> where we saw the Rathauskeller,
               the Roland and the stock exchange over which <persName key="1149">M<hi rend="ul.2">
                     <hi rend="sup">r</hi>
                  </hi> Lorenz</persName> our guide and Papa&#x2019;s friend was in raptures. <persName key="1149">M<hi rend="ul.2">
                     <hi rend="sup">r</hi>
                  </hi> Lorenz</persName> is a very funny man with a red nose and poems of which
                  <persName key="176">Papa</persName> told me the following story: one day at table
               d&#x2019;hôte he got up and said Gentlemen I will now recite one of my poems and he began
               but he was hissed down, so he goes out of the room and when the guests have calmed
               themselves down he comes back takes up a chair and threatens to kill everybody who
               interrupts him, and goes through the poem; this is the counterpart of what happened
               when we were with him when he was hissed while trying to translate some latin: in
               fact he is a noted bore on account of his sententious way of pronouncing.</p>
         </div>
